This paper is about recommender systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a new model for cross-domain collaborative filtering, which involves machine learning techniques such as matrix factorization and gradient boosting trees, indicating that it could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with data sparsity and similarity measures, which could be relevant to the subfields of social networks (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
